  "body": "<!---\r\nThanks for creating an Pull Request 💖!\r\n\r\nPlease read the following before submitting:\r\n- PRs that adds new external dependencies might take a while to review.\r\n- Keep your PR as small as possible.\r\n- Limit your PR to one type (docs, feature, refactoring, ci, or bugfix)\r\n-->\r\n\r\nCloses # <!-- Github issue # here -->\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\nHi, im very happy that zag now provides first class support for the vanilla adapter :)\r\nI used a custom implementation based on the examples already for the component library [fluid-primitives.com](https://fluid-primitives.com/).\r\n\r\nAs I now wanted to migrate, I missed some things, i added myself so i wanted to provide a PR for them.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\n- Vanilla machines do not have the option to change their props during runtime.\r\n- Component compositions, like a Dialog with a Tooltip on the trigger, were not possible with the vanilla spreadProps implementation.\r\n- some `aria-` attributes where toggled as boolean attributes and not as attributes with value strings.\r\n \r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\n- Added an `updateProps` function to the VanillaMachine so users can update props during runtime.\r\n- Updated the `spreadProps` behavior to ensure the props are correctly persisted during udpates.\r\n- Make sure boolean props that are `aria-` attributes are not applied via toggleAttribute and instead via setAttribute to ensure they are always present and only the value changes.\r\n- Also updated the vanilla component examples to use the dedicated `spreadProps` method from the class.\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n",
